    "Founded in 1471 as a refuge for Moorish and Jewish exiles from Spain, Chefchaouen developed its signature blue-wash aesthetic over centuries, with hues ranging from pale sky to deep indigo. The old medina is compact enough to explore on foot in a morning but rewards longer stays with rooftop cafés, craft workshops, and mountain hiking trails.\n\nThe Rif highlands surrounding the town offer day hikes to the Spanish mosque viewpoint and longer treks into cedar forests where Barbary macaques roam.",
