    "The Serengeti's endless plains stage the greatest wildlife spectacle on Earth — 2 million animals in an eternal, circular migration following the rains.",
    "The Serengeti ecosystem supports the world's largest intact migration of large mammals: 1.5 million wildebeest, 500,000 zebra, and 200,000 Thomson's gazelle moving in a clockwise circuit across Tanzania and Kenya. The drama peaks at the Grumeti River crossings (June) and the Mara River crossings (July–October).\n\nBeyond the migration, the Serengeti's year-round resident predator population — the highest density of lions and cheetah in Africa — ensures exceptional game viewing in every season. The Seronera Valley is particularly reliable for leopard sightings in the riverine fig trees.",
